<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="125" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1127,222,630]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,403,413,437]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Švihla, 2006" authorityName="Švihla" authorityYear="2006" box="[410,641,414,438]" class="Insecta" family="Oedemeridae" genus="Sparedrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulgaricus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[410,641,414,438]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Sparedrus bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[648,732,414,437]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very similar both in its coloration and the body form to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1852" box="[372,466,446,469]" class="Insecta" family="Oedemeridae" genus="Sparedrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orsinii">
<emphasis box="[372,466,446,469]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">S. orsinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by the absence of small glabrous areas on the elytra (
<figureCitation box="[263,360,478,502]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[113,152,1533,1552]" captionTargetBox="[144,1088,1011,1483]" captionTargetId="figure-254@1.[113,1088,1008,1497]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1-4. 1-2 – habitus of female. 1 – Sparedrus bulgaricus sp. nov.; 2 – S. orsinii Costa, 1852. 3-4 – last palpomere of female maxillary palpus. 3 – S. bulgaricus sp. nov.; 4 – S. orsinii. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325326" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325326/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Figs. 1-2</figureCitation>
, best visible in the apical third of elytra) and in the longer last palpomere of the female maxillary palpus (
<figureCitation box="[484,581,510,534]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[113,152,1533,1552]" captionTargetBox="[144,1088,1011,1483]" captionTargetId="figure-254@1.[113,1088,1008,1497]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1-4. 1-2 – habitus of female. 1 – Sparedrus bulgaricus sp. nov.; 2 – S. orsinii Costa, 1852. 3-4 – last palpomere of female maxillary palpus. 3 – S. bulgaricus sp. nov.; 4 – S. orsinii. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325326" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325326/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Figs. 3-4</figureCitation>
). In the identification key by 
<bibRefCitation author="VAZQUEZ X. A." box="[888,1058,510,534]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" refId="ref1104" refString="VAZQUEZ X. A. 2002: European Fauna of Oedemeridae. Argania Editio, Barcelona, 178 pp." type="book" year="2002">VÁZQUEZ (2002)</bibRefCitation>
it also keys to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1852" box="[234,330,542,565]" class="Insecta" family="Oedemeridae" genus="Sparedrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orsinii">
<emphasis box="[234,330,542,565]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">S. orsinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
